net.proteusframework.ui.miwt

Class AbstractAction

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.proteusframework.ui.miwt.AbstractAction
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.util.EventListener, Action, HTMLClassifier, ActionListener
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    ReflectiveAction, StateEventAction, ToggleVisibilityAction, URLExternalAction

    public abstract class AbstractAction
extends java.lang.Object
implements Action, java.lang.Cloneable
    This class provides default implementations for the Action interface. Standard behaviors like the get and set methods for Action object properties (icon, text, and enabled) are defined here. The developer need only subclass this abstract class and define the actionPerformed method.
    Author:
    Pat B. Double (double@i2rd.com)

      • appendDisplayClass

        public void appendDisplayClass(@Nullable java.lang.String string)
        Description copied from interface: HTMLClassifier
        Append a value to the display class. If no display class is set the argument becomes the display class. Otherwise a space is appended to the existing display class and then the argument.

        You can use this method to set multiple classes at once. This method does not check to see if the class names already exist in the display class string.

        Specified by:
        appendDisplayClass in interface HTMLClassifier
        Parameters:
        string - the string to append.
